    <briefdescription>
<para>Entry point for the I/O and Sockets demonstration. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This program serves as the entry point for the demonstration of cross-platform I/O and socket event monitoring. It leverages the functionality provided in the <ref refid="namespaceio__and__sockets" kindref="compound">io_and_sockets</ref> module, which sets up a TCP server that listens on a fixed port (e.g., 12345) and monitors for both incoming socket connections and console input. The demonstration continues until the user types &quot;quit&quot;, after which the server shuts down gracefully.</para>
